;-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
; Room Descriptions
;
;
NUMBER 1100
NAME Abandoned Mall, corridor
*DESCRIPTION_START
The shattered remains of a large glass and plastic sign are strewn
across the floor of the corridor from one side to the other. Each
little shard has some tiny colored writing on it, but nothing you
can put together in a meaningful way. The corridor is flanked by
an open storefront and a twisted and gaping security gate.
*DESCRIPTION_END
INDOOR_FLOOR
DARKNESS
MONSTER_GROUP 35
EXIT NE 1101
EXIT SW 1110
;
; storefront
ITEM 0 1422 VAL2=1102
; gate
ITEM 1 68 VAL2=1103 OPEN UNLOCKED
;
NUMBER 1101
NAME Abandoned Mall, corridor
*DESCRIPTION_START
Some hard plastic benches are pushed together at this intersection
of the main corridor and a small alcove leading southeast. The
benches are covered with red paint scrawls and carved initials.
To the northeast is a smashed display window.
*DESCRIPTION_END
INDOOR_FLOOR
DARKNESS
MONSTER_GROUP 35
EXIT NE 1106
EXIT SW 1100
EXIT SE 1105
;
; window
ITEM 0 475
; bench
ITEM 1 339 ADJ1=154 ADJ2=587
;
IFVERB GO 0
 MOVEGROUP 1104
 CLEARVERB
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 1102
NAME Abandoned Mall, store
*DESCRIPTION_START
Counters line the walls of this room, and some pieces of broken
mirror are scattered on the floor. Old red paint scrawls on the
counter tops and the ragged and stained carpet are covered with
a thick layer of dust.
*DESCRIPTION_END
MONSTER_GROUP 35
INDOOR_FLOOR
DARKNESS
MONSTER_GROUP 35
EXIT O 1100
;
NUMBER 1103
NAME Abandoned Mall, store
*DESCRIPTION_START
Tables, chairs, counters, in fact any furniture that wasn't bolted
down is piled all around the opening in the security gate, making
it slow and treacherous going to reach the open floor in the back
of this large room. Toward the rear are some overturned tables
with their tops facing the furniture pile. The tables have a
number of holes in them. There is a giant slogan written in red
across the back wall in a language you cannot read.
*DESCRIPTION_END
MONSTER_GROUP 35
INDOOR_FLOOR
DARKNESS
EXIT O 1100
;
NUMBER 1104
NAME Abandoned Mall, store
*DESCRIPTION_START
Two rows of plastic chairs sitting back to back run nearly the length
of this room. Low circular tables, some with built in platforms, dot
the floor. Some plastic shelving is propped against one wall amidst
some wedges of flexible plasticky material. The counter in the back
is completely covered with red paint scrawls.
*DESCRIPTION_END
INDOOR_FLOOR
DARKNESS
MONSTER_GROUP 35
EXIT O 1101
;
; chair
ITEM 0 86
;
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM UNDER 0
Under one of the chairs you see a strange measuring device with
corroded slides that once adjusted length and width. The device
is about a foot long.
*DESCRIPTION_END
;
NUMBER 1105
NAME Abandoned Mall, alcove
*DESCRIPTION_START
This small alcove off the main corridor ends before a large metal
and plastic console with a panel and a slot. Some big blocky
painted arrows chase each other around the console.
*DESCRIPTION_END
INDOOR_FLOOR
DARKNESS
MONSTER_GROUP 35
EXIT NW 1101
;
; panel
ITEM 0 282
; slot
ITEM 1 802
;
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
There is something written on it.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM READ 0
The panel reads, "Drop your card in the slot for processing."
*DESCRIPTION_END
;
NUMBER 1106
NAME Abandoned Mall, department store
*DESCRIPTION_START
Since all of the display windows were smashed, it is hard to decide
where the corridor ends and the store begins. Some tattered red
carpeting is the only good indicator. In the far rear of the store
there seems to be a great deal of damage, though closer areas look
mostly undamaged.
*DESCRIPTION_END
INDOOR_FLOOR
DARKNESS
MONSTER_GROUP 35
EXIT O 1101
EXIT N 1107
EXIT E 1108
EXIT SE 1109
;
NUMBER 1107
NAME Abandoned Mall, department store
*DESCRIPTION_START
The entire back wall of the store has collapsed but the damage is
very localized, as if any scattered debris was collected up and
pitched on the rubble pile left when the wall fell. Some picto-
graphic signs hang beside the demolished wall.
*DESCRIPTION_END
INDOOR_FLOOR
DARKNESS
MONSTER_GROUP 35
EXIT S 1106
EXIT SE 1108
;
; sign
ITEM 0 204
;
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
  ________________      ________________    ________________
 |                |    |        &       |  |                |
 | __@__  __@__   |    |      / &       |  | ___            |
 |   |      |     |    |     | /        |  |    |__         |
 |  /_\     |     |    |     ||         |  |       |__      |
 |  | |    / \    |    |     ||         |  |          |__   |
 | _____________\ |    |     | \        |  |             |  |
 |              / |    |      \ &       |  |                |
 |________________|    |_______'&_______|  |________________|

*DESCRIPTION_END
;
NUMBER 1108
NAME Abandoned Mall, department store
*DESCRIPTION_START
Counters of some composite material are pushed into a square in the
middle of the floor. The square is covered over with two plastic
panels, forming a shelter of some sort. Beside the shelter is a
blackened spot in the carpet ringed by pieces of concrete rubble.
The ceiling far above is sooty and black.
*DESCRIPTION_END
INDOOR_FLOOR
DARKNESS
MONSTER_GROUP 35
EXIT NW 1107
EXIT W 1106
EXIT S 1109
;
; shelter
ITEM 0 1423
;
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM IN 0
Inside the makeshift shelter is a thick layer of dust, and some
dessicated scraps of fabric.
*DESCRIPTION_END
;
NUMBER 1109
NAME Abandoned Mall, department store
*DESCRIPTION_START
Rows of counters and cupboards line the walls, each with the door to the
under compartment open. A stainless steel ring is screwed into each
counter near the opening. Red scrawls, each different, are painted on
the door to each compartment.
*DESCRIPTION_END
INDOOR_FLOOR
DARKNESS
MONSTER_GROUP 35
EXIT NW 1106
EXIT N 1108
;
; compartment
ITEM 0 1424
;
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM IN 0
Inside one of the compartments you find some steel studs about the size
of a fingernail.
*DESCRIPTION_END
;
NUMBER 1110
NAME Abandoned Mall, upper hub
*DESCRIPTION_START
Four corridors come together like rays around a large, circular
hole in the floor. Looking over the railing and into the hole,
you can see a dried up fountain on a level below you. A tall
sculpture winds its way to a broken skylight above. Directly
to the east is an anteroom of some kind.
*DESCRIPTION_END
INDOOR_FLOOR
MONSTER_GROUP 35
OBSCURED_DAY_LIGHT
EXIT NE 1100
EXIT SE 1111
EXIT SW 1118
EXIT NW 1119
EXIT E 1178
;
; sculpture
ITEM 0 481
;
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
This hideous structure was no doubt the height of fashion when it was
commisioned, but the years have not been kind to it. What once were elegant
bronze ivy leaves and vines now are more like a powdery green tentacles.
*DESCRIPTION_END
;
IFPREVERB CLIMB 0
 SKILLCHECK 5 0 DUMMY1
 IFVAR DUMMY1 => 0
  ECHO PLAYER You climb up the sculpture to the girder overhead.
  MOVE 1126
  ECHO ALL %N climbs up the sculpture to a girder.
 ELSE
  RANDOM DUMMY2 4 10 0
  DAMAGEPLR CRUSH DUMMY2 %N makes a misstep and falls to the floor!
  POSITION LAY
 ENDIF
 CLEARVERB
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 1111
NAME Abandoned Mall, corridor
*DESCRIPTION_START
Blue graffiti on the walls and plastic benches is mostly obliterated
by intricate red scrawls. The corridor runs northwest to southeast
with the occasional storefront still mostly intact on either side.
*DESCRIPTION_END
INDOOR_FLOOR
DARKNESS
MONSTER_GROUP 35
EXIT NW 1110
EXIT SE 1112
;
NUMBER 1112
NAME Abandoned Mall, corridor
*DESCRIPTION_START
Sooty streaks rise vertically from the front of a store to the north-
east like the bars of a cage. To the southwest, another storefront
seems mostly untouched. The doors to the store at the end of the
corridor are wedged mostly shut, though one might be able to squeeze
through a hole where a door panel was torn off.
*DESCRIPTION_END
INDOOR_FLOOR
DARKNESS
MONSTER_GROUP 35
EXIT NW 1111
;
; burnt store
ITEM 0 1425 ADJ1=44  VAL2=1116
; intact storefront
ITEM 1 1422 ADJ1=507 VAL2=1115
; hole
ITEM 2 79 VAL2=1113
;
NUMBER 1113
NAME Abandoned Mall, store
*DESCRIPTION_START
Just inside the wedged doors is a slag pile of blackened melted plastic.
At the edges of the pile not all the plastic is melted and you can see
the twisted ends of plastic clothing hangers. The ceiling is black with
soot and it covers the walls and even the carpet. Some blackened furniture
is piled up like a barricade in the rear of the store.
*DESCRIPTION_END
INDOOR_FLOOR
DARKNESS
MONSTER_GROUP 35
EXIT O 1111
;
NUMBER 1114
NAME Abandoned Mall, corridor
*DESCRIPTION_START
This corridor must once have stretched to the southwest, but it looks
like the building's structure has collapsed completely. What was the
second floor, as well as the usual parts of this one, now fill this
passage entirely.
*DESCRIPTION_END
MONSTER_GROUP 60
INDOOR_FLOOR
DARKNESS
EXIT NE 1130
;
NUMBER 1115
NAME Abandoned Mall, store
*DESCRIPTION_START
This room has torn up carpeting and metal panels on the walls, but is
otherwise empty except for a few shell casings scattered around in the
thick dust. The store across the hall looks like it was burned out.
*DESCRIPTION_END
INDOOR_FLOOR
DARKNESS
MONSTER_GROUP 35
EXIT O 1112
;
NUMBER 1116
NAME Abandoned Mall, store
*DESCRIPTION_START
Rows of metal racks hold thin plastic boxes twisted and melted around
warped disks. There is no carpeting, just scorched concrete and a
metal desk in the back of the room.
*DESCRIPTION_END
INDOOR_FLOOR
DARKNESS
EXIT O 1112
MONSTER_GROUP 35
;
; desk
ITEM 0 201
;
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM UNDER 0
Beneath the desk, amid ash and soot are some small pieces of ceramic.
*DESCRIPTION_END
;
NUMBER 1117
NAME Abandoned Mall, corridor
*DESCRIPTION_START
A breeze, fresh with the smells of the wastelands outside, blows in
through some chinks in the rubble pile that stands before you to the
northwest. Although some of the pieces of rubble are recognizable as
parts of storefronts, none of them remains intact. This wing of the
mall has been utterly destroyed.
*DESCRIPTION_END
INDOOR_FLOOR
DARKNESS
MONSTER_GROUP 60
EXIT SE 1130
;
IFVERB SMELL -1
  ECHO PLAYER You can clearly detect the smell of fresh air coming through\
the cracks in the rubble.
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 1118
NAME Abandoned Mall, corridor
*DESCRIPTION_START
An enormous amount of debris has fallen from the ceiling, blocking off
any further progress to the southwest. Large slabs of concrete which once
formed the structure of the building now lie in a jumbled heap, with
broken bits and pieces facing every which way.
*DESCRIPTION_END
MONSTER_GROUP 35
INDOOR_FLOOR
DARKNESS
EXIT NE 1110
;
; gap
ITEM 0 459 ADJ1=210
;
IFPREVERB GO 0
   CLEARVERB
   RANDOM DUMMY1 3 8 0
   ECHO PLAYER With only minor difficulty, you squeeze through the gap.
   ECHO OTHERS %n squeezes into the gap.
   AFFECT 1120
   ECHO OTHERS %n squeezes in through a gap in the concrete slabs.
   MOVE 1120
   ADD ROUNDTIME DUMMY1
ENDIF
;
;
IFVERB SEARCH -1
   ECHO PLAYER You've found a gap between slabs of concrete that you might be able to squeeze through, as long as you don't get stuck.
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 1119
NAME Abandoned Mall, corridor
*DESCRIPTION_START
Heavy slabs of ceiling concrete have collapsed, blocking access to the
northwest and knocking loose much more of the infrastructure that has
fallen and piled up on the floor below. Whatever was here in the past
is now lost to the broken and twisted debris.
*DESCRIPTION_END
MONSTER_GROUP 35
INDOOR_FLOOR
DARKNESS
EXIT SE 1110
;
NUMBER 1120
NAME Abandoned Mall, rubble
*DESCRIPTION_START
Once amidst the rubble, the interstices between the slabs of concrete
enlarge considerably, giving you ample room to maneuver.  Although
the position of the concrete and debris seems to be random, the passage
is too clear and to close to human dimensions to have been solely the
result of a structural failure.
*DESCRIPTION_END
INDOOR_FLOOR
DARKNESS
EXIT O 1118
EXIT W 1121
EXIT SW 1122
;
NUMBER 1121
NAME Abandoned Mall, rubble
*DESCRIPTION_START
Some dusty rags and tattered blankets are piled up like a little nest
amidst the broken concrete slabs. It looks like they are very old and
about to fall apart. Just over the nest, a tiny nook has been hollowed
out from the heaped debris. From within, a small statue of Kaliban
stands a silent vigil over this humble home.
*DESCRIPTION_END
INDOOR_FLOOR
DARKNESS
EXIT E 1120
;
; small statue of Kaliban
ITEM 0 346 ADJ1=294
EXTEND 0 of Kaliban
;
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
This simple carving depicts the god Kaliban, dressed in coarse rags,
distributing small bags of coins to some needy children who cling to
his feet and ankles.
*DESCRIPTION_END
;
NUMBER 1122
NAME Abandoned Mall, rubble
*DESCRIPTION_START
A huge concrete slab tilts at a steep angle, allowing passage beneath
it to the northeast and the southwest. A worn path beneath it marks it
as an oft-used passage through the debris. Smaller chunks of cement and
rubble make the passage arduous, but don't block the way.
*DESCRIPTION_END
INDOOR_FLOOR
DARKNESS
EXIT NE 1120
EXIT SW 1123
;
NUMBER 1123
NAME Abandoned Mall, rubble
*DESCRIPTION_START
You have to maneuver very carefully not to fall through the rough-
edged hole in the floor. Apparently, some of the rubble gave way
and crashed down to the lower level. Perhaps this corridor through
the wreckage is not as stable as you thought.
*DESCRIPTION_END
DARKNESS
INDOOR_FLOOR
EXIT NE 1122
EXIT D 1129
;
NUMBER 1129
NAME Abandoned Mall, store
*DESCRIPTION_START
You can see from the collapsed front of the store that it must have
been sealed off from the rest of the mall for some time. A few
plastic racks remain upright among piles of dust and rust. There
is a very large hole in the ceiling you can get to by climbing
a pile of rubble.
*DESCRIPTION_END
INDOOR_FLOOR
DARKNESS
EXIT U 1123
EXIT W 1124
EXIT S 1125
;
; (plastic) rack
ITEM 0 539  ADJ1=587
;
NUMBER 1124
NAME Abandoned Mall, store
*DESCRIPTION_START
Painted on the wall in bright orange are stick figures engaged in
different activities. Some are obvious, like a figure running, but
some are holding different sorts of objects whose purposes are
obscure. The floor is painted with strange colored lines and curves
which seem to be part of a pattern.
*DESCRIPTION_END
INDOOR_FLOOR
DARKNESS
EXIT E 1129
EXIT SE 1125
;
NUMBER 1125
NAME Abandoned Mall, store
*DESCRIPTION_START
Some rubble and debris from the collapsed entrance has nearly tipped over a
counter that was near the wall when it fell. Puffs of dust rise from the
floor with each footstep, leading you to believe no one has trod here in a
very long time.
*DESCRIPTION_END
INDOOR_FLOOR
DARKNESS
EXIT N 1129
EXIT NW 1124
;
; counter
ITEM 0 470 LOCKED CLOSED VAL1=60
;
NUMBER 1126
NAME Abandoned Mall, girder
*DESCRIPTION_START
You find yourself just below the hole in the skylight, balancing on
a girder above a drop of two stories. Below you seems to be the
intersecting hub of four corridors. Some strange twisting sculpture
rises from the top level to just below you.
*DESCRIPTION_END
LIMITED_MOVEMENT
DAY_LIGHT
;
; sculpture
ITEM 0 481
;
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
This hideous structure was no doubt the height of fashion when it was
commisioned, but the years have not been kind to it. What once were elegant
bronze ivy leaves and vines now are more like a powdery green tentacles.
*DESCRIPTION_END
; hole
ITEM 1 79 VAL2=1189
;
IFPREVERB CLIMB 0
 SKILLCHECK 5 0 DUMMY1
 IFVAR DUMMY1 => 0
  ECHO PLAYER You climb down the sculpture to the floor.
  MOVE 1110
  ECHO ALL %N climbs down the sculpture to the floor.
 ELSE
  RANDOM DUMMY2 4 10 0
  DAMAGEPLR CRUSH DUMMY2 %N makes a misstep and falls to the floor!
  MOVE 1110
  AFFECT 1110
  ECHO OTHERS %n comes plummeting down from above and falls to the floor
  POSITION LAY
 ENDIF
 CLEARVERB
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 1130
NAME Abandoned Mall, lower hub
*DESCRIPTION_START
Four corridors intersect around a dry, empty fountain which is lined
with faded blue tiles. A heap of rusted metal in the center marks
the spot where an elaborate system of jets and pipes once delighted
visitors. Above the fountain is a large round hole through which you
can view part of the upper level. Directly to the east is an anteroom.
*DESCRIPTION_END
MONSTER_GROUP 60
INDOOR_FLOOR
OBSCURED_DAY_LIGHT
EXIT NE 1131
EXIT SE 1140
EXIT SW 1114
EXIT NW 1117
EXIT E 1179
;
; fountain
ITEM 0 197
;
NUMBER 1131
NAME Abandoned Mall, corridor
*DESCRIPTION_START
A jagged plastic stump juts up where something was broken off two
feet above a concrete floor pocked by gouges and long striations.
On one side of the corridor is a shop with a caved-in ceiling and
on the other is a half-closed security gate.
*DESCRIPTION_END
MONSTER_GROUP 60
INDOOR_FLOOR
DARKNESS
EXIT SW 1130
EXIT NE 1133
;
; gate
ITEM 0 68 VAL2=1132 OPEN UNLOCKED
;store
ITEM 1 1425
;
IFPREVERB GO 1
   ECHO PLAYER You'd have to be about two inches tall to have even a hope\
of entering this store.
   CLEARVERB
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 1132
NAME Abandoned Mall, store
*DESCRIPTION_START
This long, skinny store has alcoves with little doors in the back built
one atop the other along one wall. The alcoves are open in the front,
but close examination reveals little shards of glass scattered through
them. In the back are a series of little booths, each with a plastic
bench, with walls only three feet high. At intervals, piles of rusty
flakes spot the floor. Mixed in one pile are a number of little shiny
studs.
*DESCRIPTION_END
INDOOR_FLOOR
DARKNESS
MONSTER_GROUP 60
EXIT O 1131
;
; alcove
ITEM 0 803
; booth
ITEM 1 1427
;
NUMBER 1133
NAME Abandoned Mall, corridor
*DESCRIPTION_START
Two plastic benches sit beside a brown plastic bucket with a tall
plastic plant in it. Some leaves are stretched and deformed, as if
somone tried to pull them off without much luck. A large red plastic
sign hangs crookedly over a door to the southeast. To the northwest
you see a room with plastic tables and chairs.
*DESCRIPTION_END
MONSTER_GROUP 60
INDOOR_FLOOR
DARKNESS
EXIT SW 1131
EXIT NE 1135
;
; door
ITEM 0 66 VAL2=1134 OPEN UNLOCKED
; room
ITEM 1 1428 VAL2=1139
;
NUMBER 1134
NAME Abandoned Mall, store
*DESCRIPTION_START
This room is long and wide, with a high ceiling. Tiles of a strange
material are scattered across the floor, sometimes lined up and
orderly, but mostly askew. At regular intervals across the entire
floor, holes have been drilled in the concrete beneath large piles
of dust kicked up as you move.
*DESCRIPTION_END
INDOOR_FLOOR
DARKNESS
MONSTER_GROUP 60
EXIT O 1133
;
NUMBER 1135
NAME Abandoned Mall, corridor
*DESCRIPTION_START
The corridor ends at a wall of polished black granite with a low
door leading inside. Some alcoves in the granite are full of
dust. To the southwest, at the end of the corridor, you can see
light glint off the elevator.
*DESCRIPTION_END
MONSTER_GROUP 60
INDOOR_FLOOR
DARKNESS
EXIT SW 1133
;
; alcove
ITEM 0 803
; alcove
ITEM 1 803
; door
ITEM 2 66 ADJ1=396  VAL2=1136 CLOSED
