IFVERB GO 2
 MOVEGROUP 1136
 CLEARVERB
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 1136
NAME Abandoned Mall, department store
*DESCRIPTION_START
Once inside the low doorway, this entrance is a shambles. To the north,
the far wall and the ceiling have tumbled down in a mess of concrete,
plastic tubing and rust. To the east and southeast the damage is much
less.
*DESCRIPTION_END
INDOOR_FLOOR
DARKNESS
MONSTER_GROUP 60
EXIT O 1135
EXIT E 1137
EXIT SE 1138
;
; crevice (hidden)
ITEM 0 63 VAL2=1127
;
IFPREVERB SEARCH -1
 ECHO PLAYER You find a crevice between pieces of concrete you might be able to crawl through.
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 1137
NAME Abandoned Mall, department store
*DESCRIPTION_START
The floor is made from tessellated squares of polished stone. The
resultant pattern radiates black lines like spokes in a wheel
with alternating beige and white wedges between. The pattern is
discernable where it is not covered with dust and the occasional
pile of rust and broken glass.
*DESCRIPTION_END
INDOOR_FLOOR
DARKNESS
MONSTER_GROUP 60
EXIT W 1136
EXIT S 1138
;
NUMBER 1138
NAME Abandoned Mall, department store
*DESCRIPTION_START
This part of the store is largely undisturbed. Two tall chairs with
foot pedals face a wall of unbroken mirrors and drawered supply
cabinets. The seats of the chairs have long ago decayed leaving
uncomfortable bolts sticking up.
*DESCRIPTION_END
MONSTER_GROUP 60
INDOOR_FLOOR
DARKNESS
EXIT N 1137
EXIT NW 1136
;
; drawer
ITEM 0 384
; cabinet
ITEM 1 821
;
NUMBER 1139
NAME Abandoned Mall, store
*DESCRIPTION_START
The furnishings in this room are largely intact and unmolested and
seem to be made mostly of bright yellow molded plastic. The chairs
spin on plastic poles and the tabletops are attached to the wall
by sturdy plastic bars. The counter has three square holes cut in
the top.
*DESCRIPTION_END
INDOOR_FLOOR
DARKNESS
MONSTER_GROUP 60
EXIT O 1133
;
; counter
ITEM 0 470
;
NUMBER 1140
NAME Abandoned Mall, corridor
*DESCRIPTION_START
This corridor stretches to the northwest and southeast from here, connecting
the central hub of the mall to the stores of this branch. On opposite sides
of the hallway are two stores, one accessible through a door, and the
other through a broken security gate.
*DESCRIPTION_END
MONSTER_GROUP 60
INDOOR_FLOOR
DARKNESS
EXIT NW 1130
EXIT SE 1143
;
; doorway
ITEM 0 65 VAL2=1142 OPEN UNLOCKED
; gate
ITEM 1 68 VAL2=1141 OPEN UNLOCKED
;
NUMBER 1141
NAME Abandoned Mall, store
*DESCRIPTION_START
Holes drilled at even intervals in the walls indicate where shelves
must have been. Now nothing remains of them but dust, rust and
broken glass. A counter made of some brown plastic material, its surface
grained to look like wood, is pushed against the back wall. Torn and empty
plastic packing materials are spread across the floor, many molded with
the impression of a knife.
*DESCRIPTION_END
INDOOR_FLOOR
DARKNESS
MONSTER_GROUP 60
EXIT O 1140
;
; counter
ITEM 0 470
;
NUMBER 1142
NAME Abandoned Mall, store
*DESCRIPTION_START
Some colorful plastic cabinets are leaned together and pushed over
throughout this room. Some have pictures of humans with beam weapons
or swords, and some are decorated with cartoonish figures. Empty
sockets line the ceiling, some with broken glass in them. Broken glass
from the front of the cabinets is scattered across the floor. There is
a small box with some writing on it hanging on the wall about three and
a half feet off the floor.
*DESCRIPTION_END
INDOOR_FLOOR
DARKNESS
MONSTER_GROUP 60
EXIT O 1140
