NUMBER 1163
NAME Sublevel 2, electrical conduit
*DESCRIPTION_START
Several of the casings of the cables in this room have been severely damaged,
and the metal wires are exposed in a number of places. The walls of the
conduit are charred and pitted, and the entire room has a distinctive acrid
smell. The conduit continues to the north and south.
*DESCRIPTION_END
INDOOR_FLOOR
DARKNESS
EXIT S 1162
EXIT N 1164
;
IFPREVERB north -1
   CLEARVERB
   IFVAR PVAL50 > 0
      ECHO PLAYER Your movements seem to have disturbed a live wire.
      ECHO ALL A massive electrical discharge arcs between the damaged\
cables lining the wall of the conduit. Unfortunately, your head is the path\
of least resistance. All activity in your brain comes rapidly to a halt.
      KILL ALL
      AFFECT 1160
      ECHO ALL You hear a small crackle of electricity arcing across\
the contacts of one of the switches.
      AFFECT 1163
      STOP
   ENDIF
   AFFECT 1164
   IFVAR PLRSINROOM > 0
     AFFECT 1163
     ECHO PLAYER Someone is blocking the conduit ahead of you.
   ELSE
