NUMBER 1165
NAME Sublevel 2, electrical utility room
*DESCRIPTION_START
Huge power cables wrapped in black insulating plastic cover all available
walls space in this spartan concrete room. A weak yellowish light in a
steel wire cage dangles from the ceiling. A large number of the cables
go out of the room through a low opening near the floor. On the wall
opposite the opening is a large switch with a thick wire leading out from
it and down the wall. Some sticky strands of secreted material coat a
number of the cables as well as the switch.
*DESCRIPTION_END
FIXED_LIGHT
INDOOR_FLOOR
;
ITEM 0 72 ADJ1=396 VAL2=1164
; ITEM 0 is a low opening
ITEM 1 422 ADJ1=178
;
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
Although the opening is small, even a large human could probably fit
through laying down and working slowly through.
*DESCRIPTION_END
;
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM READ 1
The switch is labeled with a small tag reading:

                        CAUTION!

               BACKUP POWER SYSTEM OVERRIDE

This circuit is protected by anti-tampering devices. Do not attempt
to change it without first disconnecting the main power couplings.

On the back of the tag are some strange words written in a careful hand:

BLACK   OCHRE   WHITE   BLACK   GREY

There is no clue to their meaning, however.

*DESCRIPTION_END
;
IFPREVERB EXAMINE 1
   ECHO PLAYER There is some writing on the switch.
   CLEARVERB
ENDIF
;
;
ifpreverb go 0
   clearverb
   ifvar RAC ! 3
      position lay
      echo player You lay down in preparation to enter the opening.
      echo others %n lays down and prepares to enter the opening.
   endif
   affect 1164
   ifvar PLRSINROOM > 0
      affect 1165
      echo player You can't move ahead because someone else is blocking\
the conduit ahead of you.
   else
      affect 1165
      echo player You work your way through the opening.
      echo others %n moves into the low opening.
      move 1164
      affect 1164
      echo others %n works %h way in from the north.
      affect 1164
   endif
endif
;
;Scripts for elevator shaft
;
NUMBER 1178
NAME Abandoned Mall, anteroom
*DESCRIPTION_START
Ragged bits of pale pink carpet cover most of the concrete floor of this
small chamber. On one wall, a large mirror hangs slightly askew from a
single remaining mount. Opposite the mirror is a wide metal door. On
the adjacent wall, a large numeral '2' is still just barely visible,
although its color has faded to nearly that of the wall. Next to the
door is a small panel with a round plastic button set into it.
*DESCRIPTION_END
INDOOR_FLOOR
DARKNESS
MONSTER_GROUP 35
EXIT W 1110
;
ITEM 0 247 ADJ1=265 ADJ2=587
;ITEM 0 is a round plastic button
ITEM 1 350 ADJ1=348 ADJ2=192 VAL2=1180 CLOSED
;ITEM 1 is a wide metal door
ITEM 3 332 ADJ1=71
ITEM 4 745
;
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 4
You see a hideous face staring back at you.
*DESCRIPTION_END
;
VARIABLE button_lit
;
IFENTRY
   IFVAR PLRSINROOM = 1
     EQUAL button_lit 0
   ENDIF
ENDIF
;
IFVERB push 0
   IFVAR button_lit = 0
      ECHO ALL The button glows softly.
      EQUAL button_lit 1
   ELSE
      ECHO ALL The button winks out momentarily and then continues to glow\
softly.
   ENDIF
ENDIF
;
IFPREVERB look 0
   CLEARVERB
   IFVAR button_lit > 0
      ECHO PLAYER The button is glowing with a soft yellow light.
   ELSE
      ECHO PLAYER The button is dark.
   ENDIF
ENDIF
;
IFPREVERB look 1
   CLEARVERB
   IFNOITEM 2
      ECHO PLAYER This wide aluminum door slides horizontally from a\
hidden track somewhere in the ceiling or floor. It has no handle or latch\
visible from this side. It is tightly closed.
      ELSE
      ECHO PLAYER This battered aluminum door hangs tenuously from an overhead\
track. The two panels of the door have been forced apart, forming a dark\
opening big enough to enter. You can see something else just beyond the door,\
but you can't quite tell what it is.
   ENDIF
ENDIF
;
IFPREVERB open 1
   ECHO PLAYER You struggle to open the door, but can't budge it.
   ECHO OTHERS %n struggles with the door, but cannot open it.
   CLEARVERB
ENDIF
;
IFPREVERB break 1
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER You break through the flimsy door with ease, creating a dark\
opening in it.
   ECHO OTHERS %n breaks open the stubborn door, creating a dark opening in it.
   ECHO PLAYER  [Round: 5 sec]
   ADD ROUNDTIME 5
   NEWITEM 2 72 ADJ1=87 VAL2=1180
   EXTEND 1 with a dark opening broken through it
ENDIF
;
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM IN 2
In the dark opening you can see a number of cables and wires, as well as an
old, corroded chain, but you can't see a floor at all. Although the cables
look like they'd collapse in an instant, the chain still looks quite sturdy,
despite the corrosion on its outside layer. You should probably try to jump
to the chain inside rather than just rushing headlong through the opening.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 2
It looks as if this opening in the door was created by someone trying to
force it apart. You can just make out something deep within it.
*DESCRIPTION_END
;
IFPREVERB go 2
   CLEARVERB
   IFVAR RAC ! 8
      ECHO PLAYER You go through the opening, only to find that the next room\
has no floor. You find yourself falling freely for a moment, and then you\
impact the hard surface beneath.
      ECHO OTHERS %n goes through the opening and disappears out of sight.
      AFFECT 1180
      ECHO ALL %n rushes through the opening in the shaft and plummets down\
into the darkness. A moment later, you hear a distict thud from below.
      AFFECT 1181
      MOVE 1181
      ECHO OTHERS %n comes falling down the shaft from above.
      DAMAGE CRUSH 30 You hear the sound of flesh impacting a solid surface.
      POSITION LAY
      AFFECT 1178
   ELSE
      ECHO PLAYER You drift slowly through the opening.
      ECHO OTHERS %n goes through the opening and disappears out of sight.
      MOVE 1180
      AFFECT 1181
      ECHO OTHERS %n drifts in through the opening.
      AFFECT 1178
   ENDIF
ENDIF
;
IFTOUCH 3
   ECHO PLAYER You can't quite reach the chain from here.
ENDIF
;
IFVERB jump 3
   CLEARVERB
   IFVAR RAC = 8
      ECHO PLAYER You float out to the chain with ease.
      ECHO OTHERS %n floats out the the chain with ease.
      AFFECT 1180
      ECHO OTHERS %n floats in through the opening to the chain.
      MOVE 1180
      AFFECT 1178
      STOP
   ENDIF
   ECHO PLAYER You attempt to jump through the opening to the chain.
   RANDOM DUMMY1 1 100 0
   ADD DUMMY1 AGI
   IFVAR DUMMY1 < 120
      ECHO PLAYER You miss the chain and fall down the shaft.
      ECHO OTHERS %n jumps through the opening and falls down the shaft.
      AFFECT 1180
      ECHO OTHERS %n comes flying towards the chain, but misses and falls.
      AFFECT 1181
      MOVE 1181
      ECHO OTHERS %n comes falling down the shaft from above.
      DAMAGE CRUSH 30 You hear the sound of flesh impacting a solid surface.
      POSITION LAY
      AFFECT 1178
   ELSE
      ECHO OTHERS %n jumps through the opening and grabs the chain inside.
      ECHO PLAYER You jump through the opening and grab the chain.
      AFFECT 1180
      MOVE 1180
     ECHO OTHERS %n jumps towards the chain, and manages to grab it and stop.
   ENDIF
ENDIF
;
;
NUMBER 1180
NAME Abandoned Mall, vertical shaft
*DESCRIPTION_START
Straight vertical walls form a square sectioned shaft extending both above
and below. Although this shaft has no floor for some ways down there are
plenty of footholds and handholds, as well as an old chain, which keep you
from plummeting down the shaft into the darkness below. There is a
rectangular opening in the wall here, and two mangled doors hang loosely on
their tracks on either side. You could probably climb down the chain from
here.
*DESCRIPTION_END
DARKNESS
INDOOR_FLOOR
;
ITEM 0 332 ADJ1=71
ITEM 1 72 ADJ1=87 VAL2=1178
;
IFPREVERB CLIMB 0
   CLEARVERB
   IFVAR RAC = 8
      ECHO PLAYER You drift slowly down the shaft.
      ECHO OTHERS %n drifts slowly down the shaft.
      AFFECT 1181
      MOVE 1181
      ECHO OTHERS %n drifts down the shaft from above.
      AFFECT 1180
      STOP
   ENDIF
   ECHO PLAYER You start down the chain with care.
   SKILLCHECK 5 45 DUMMY1
   IFVAR DUMMY1 < 0
      ECHO PLAYER You loose your grip and fall down the shaft!
      ECHO OTHERS %n starts down the chain, but slips and falls!
      AFFECT 1181
      MOVE 1181
      ECHO OTHERS %n comes falling down the shaft from above.
      DAMAGE CRUSH 30 You hear the sound of flesh impacting a solid surface.
      POSITION LAY
   ELSE
      ECHO PLAYER You climb safely down the chain to the bottom of the shaft.
      ECHO OTHERS %n climbs safely down the chain.
      AFFECT 1181
      MOVE 1181
      ECHO OTHERS %n comes down the shaft from above.
      AFFECT 1180
   ENDIF
ENDIF
;
IFTOUCH 1
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER The opening is too far to reach.
ENDIF
;
IFPREVERB GO 1
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER The opening is too far to reach. You'll have to jump there.
ENDIF
;
IFVERB JUMP 1
   CLEARVERB
   IFVAR RAC ! 8
      RANDOM DUMMY1 1 100 0
      ADD DUMMY1 AGI
      IFVAR DUMMY1 < 115
         ECHO PLAYER You misjudge the distance to the opening and fall down\
the shaft.
         ECHO OTHERS %n leaps for the opening and misses!
         AFFECT 1181
         MOVE 1181
         ECHO OTHERS %n comes falling down the shaft from above.
       DAMAGE CRUSH 30 You hear the sound of flesh impacting a solid surface.
         POSITION LAY
         AFFECT 1178
      ELSE
         ECHO PLAYER You leap right through the opening.
         ECHO OTHERS %n leaps right through the opening.
         AFFECT 1178
         MOVE 1178
         ECHO OTHERS %n comes leaping through the opening in the doors.
      ENDIF
   ELSE
      ECHO PLAYER You drift over to the opening and through it.
      ECHO OTHERS %n drifts over to the opening ant through it.
      AFFECT 1178
      MOVE 1178
      ECHO OTHERS %n comes floating through the opening.
   ENDIF
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 1181
NAME Abandoned Mall, shaft bottom
*DESCRIPTION_START
The floor of this room is covered with nuts, bolts, rivets, and other
bits and pieces of hardware. There is a large pulley secured to floor
near the exact center of the room. The walls of the shaft are wide and
rise in a nearly perfect square up into the darkness overhead. A rusty
chain dangles from above over the scattered bones of some hapless
adventurer who perished here before you.
*DESCRIPTION_END
DARKNESS
INDOOR_FLOOR
;
ITEM 0 352 ADJ1=374 ADJ2=164
;ITEM 0 is a skull
ITEM 1 233 ADJ1=222
;ITEM 1 are some bones
ITEM 2 550 ADJ1=294 VAL1=35 VAL2=1182 VAL3=56 CLOSED LOCKED
;ITEM 2 is a trapdoor portal to rm 1182
ITEM 3 332 ADJ1=71
;ITEM 3 is a chain for climbing to 1180
;
IFPREVERB SEARCH -1
   RANDOM DUMMY1 1 100 0
   ADD DUMMY1 PER
   IFVAR DUMMY1 > 120
     ECHO PLAYER You find an old skull among the scattered bones.
     CLEARVERB
     ADD ROUNDTIME 5
   ENDIF
   IFVAR DUMMY1 > 145
     ECHO PLAYER You also find a small square trapdoor set into the floor.
   ENDIF
ENDIF
;
IFPREVERB BREAK 2
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER You attempt to break open the trapdoor.
   ECHO OTHERS %n attempts to break open the trapdoor.
   ECHO PLAYER  [Round: 5 sec]
   ADD ROUNDTIME 5
   RANDOM DUMMY1 1 100 0
   ADD DUMMY1 STR
   IFVAR DUMMY1 > 185
      ECHO ALL The trapdoor breaks into several pieces, which hang limply from the hinges.
      REMOVEITEM 2
      NEWITEM 2 550 ADJ1=454 VAL1=35 VAL2=1182 VAL3=56 OPEN UNLOCKED
      AFFECT 1182
      ECHO ALL Someone breaks open the trapdoor with a mighty blow from above.
      REMOVEITEM 2
      NEWITEM 2 550 ADJ1=454 VAL1=35 VAL2=1181 VAL3=56 OPEN UNLOCKED
      AFFECT 1181
   ELSE
      IFVAR DUMMY1 > 155
         ECHO ALL The trapdoor cracks and splinters around the latch, but remains intact.
         REMOVEITEM 2
         NEWITEM 2 550 ADJ1=83 VAL1=35 VAL2=1182 VAL3=56 CLOSED UNLOCKED
         AFFECT 1182
         ECHO ALL Someone cracks and splinters the trapdoor with a blow from above.
         REMOVEITEM 2
         NEWITEM 2 550 ADJ1=83 VAL1=35 VAL2=1181 VAL3=56 CLOSED UNLOCKED
         AFFECT 1181
      ELSE
         ECHO ALL The trapdoor is undamaged by the blow.
         AFFECT 1182
         ECHO ALL Someone pounds on the trapdoor from above.
         AFFECT 1181
      ENDIF
   ENDIF
ENDIF
;
IFPREVERB CLIMB 3
   CLEARVERB
   IFVAR RAC = 8
      ECHO PLAYER You drift slowly up the shaft.
      ECHO OTHERS %n drifts slowly up the shaft.
      AFFECT 1180
      MOVE 1180
      ECHO OTHERS %n drifts up shaft from below.
      AFFECT 1181
      STOP
   ENDIF
   ECHO PLAYER You start up the chain with care.
   SKILLCHECK 5 50 DUMMY1
   IFVAR DUMMY1 < 0
      ECHO PLAYER You loose your grip and fall down the shaft!
      ECHO OTHERS %n starts up the chain, but slips and falls!
      DAMAGE CRUSH 30 You hear the solid thud of flesh impacting a hard surface.
      POSITION LAY
   ELSE
      ECHO PLAYER You climb safely up the chain.
      ECHO OTHERS %n climbs safely up the chain.
      AFFECT 1180
      MOVE 1180
      ECHO OTHERS %n comes up the chain from shaft below.
      AFFECT 1181
   ENDIF
ENDIF
;
;
NUMBER 1182
NAME Abandoned Mall, cubical room
*DESCRIPTION_START
This tiny room is almost cubical inside, being as wide and deep as it is
tall. It was at one time tastefully appointed with paneling and brass,
but now the panels are rotted and worm-eaten and the brass has corroded to
shapeless green blobs. A lattice of white plastic decorates the ceiling and
a wide metal door opens across almost all of one wall.
*DESCRIPTION_END
DARKNESS
INDOOR_FLOOR
;
ITEM 1 350 ADJ1=348 ADJ2=192 VAL2=1179 CLOSED
;ITEM 1 is a wide metal door
ITEM 2 550 ADJ1=294 VAL1=35 VAL2=1181 VAL3=56 CLOSED LOCKED
;ITEM 2 is a trapdoor portal to rm 1181
;
IFPREVERB SEARCH -1
   RANDOM DUMMY1 1 100 0
   ADD DUMMY1 PER
   IFVAR DUMMY1 > 145
     ECHO PLAYER You find a small square trapdoor set into the ceiling.
     CLEARVERB
   ENDIF
ENDIF
;
IFPREVERB BREAK 2
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER You attempt to break open the trapdoor.
   ECHO OTHERS %n attempts to break open the trapdoor.
   ECHO PLAYER  [Round: 5 sec]
   ADD ROUNDTIME 5
   RANDOM DUMMY1 1 100 0
   ADD DUMMY1 STR
   IFVAR DUMMY1 > 185
      ECHO ALL The trapdoor breaks into several pieces, which hang limply from the hinges.
      REMOVEITEM 2
      NEWITEM 2 550 ADJ1=454 VAL1=35 VAL2=1181 VAL3=56 OPEN UNLOCKED
      AFFECT 1181
      ECHO ALL Someone breaks open the trapdoor with a mighty blow from below.
      REMOVEITEM 2
      NEWITEM 2 550 ADJ1=454 VAL1=35 VAL2=1182 VAL3=56 OPEN UNLOCKED
      AFFECT 1182
   ELSE
      IFVAR DUMMY1 > 155
         ECHO ALL The trapdoor cracks and splinters around the latch, but remains intact.
         REMOVEITEM 2
         NEWITEM 2 550 ADJ1=83 VAL1=35 VAL2=1181 VAL3=56 CLOSED UNLOCKED
         AFFECT 1181
         ECHO ALL Someone cracks and splinters the trapdoor with a blow from below.
         REMOVEITEM 2
         NEWITEM 2 550 ADJ1=83 VAL1=35 VAL2=1182 VAL3=56 CLOSED UNLOCKED
         AFFECT 1182
      ELSE
         ECHO ALL The trapdoor is undamaged by the blow.
         AFFECT 1181
         ECHO ALL Someone pounds on the trapdoor from below.
         AFFECT 1182
      ENDIF
   ENDIF
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 1179
NAME Abandoned Mall, anteroom
*DESCRIPTION_START
Ragged bits of pale pink carpet cover most of the concrete floor of this
small chamber. Many shards of mirrored glass lie strewn about the room, as
if someone had smashed them all and left the bits behind. Opposite the
mirror is a wide metal door. On the adjacent wall, a large numeral '1' is
still just barely visible, although its color has faded to nearly that of
the wall. Next to the door is a small panel with a round plastic button
set into it.
*DESCRIPTION_END
INDOOR_FLOOR
MONSTER_GROUP 60
DARKNESS
EXIT W 1130
;
ITEM 0 247 ADJ1=265 ADJ2=587
;ITEM 0 is a round plastic button
ITEM 1 350 ADJ1=348 ADJ2=192 VAL2=1182 CLOSED
;ITEM 1 is a wide metal door
;
VARIABLE button2_lit
;
IFENTRY
   IFVAR PLRSINROOM = 1
     EQUAL button2_lit 0
   ENDIF
ENDIF
;
IFVERB push 0
   IFVAR button2_lit = 0
      ECHO ALL The button glows softly.
      EQUAL button2_lit 1
   ELSE
      ECHO ALL The button winks out momentarily and then continues to glow\
softly.
   ENDIF
ENDIF
;
IFPREVERB look 0
   CLEARVERB
   IFVAR button2_lit > 0
      ECHO PLAYER The button is glowing with a soft yellow light.
   ELSE
      ECHO PLAYER The button is dark.
   ENDIF
ENDIF
;
;
;
NUMBER 1189
NAME Wasteland, dunes
*DESCRIPTION_START
Windblown sand has made this entire region into a desolate ocean of
brown. Sand dunes rise all around, but in this valley between them
you see a strange sight. The blowing sands have revealed a metal
framed glass window in the ground!
*DESCRIPTION_END
DAY_LIGHT
WASTE
;
; window
ITEM 0 475
; dune
ITEM 1 609 VAL2=1300 ADJ1=294 ADJ2=274
;
VARIABLE brokwin
;
IFENTRY
   IFVAR PLRSINROOM = 1
     EQUAL brokwin 0
   ENDIF
ENDIF
;
EXTEND 0 in the ground
IFPREVERB BREAK 0
 IFVAR brokwin = 0
  ECHO PLAYER You break a large hole in the window!
  ECHO OTHERS %N breaks a large hole in the window!
  EQUAL brokwin 1
  NEWITEM 2 79 ADJ1=178 VAL2=1126
  EXTEND 0 with a large hole broken in it
 ELSE
  ECHO PLAYER You decide the hole is large enough without more breakage.
 ENDIF
 CLEARVERB
ENDIF
;
IFPREVERB LOOK 0
   IFVAR brokwin = 0
     ECHO PLAYER A square lattice of metal holds together the glass panes which make up\
the window. Although the glass looks thick, a solid blow could probably break through it.
   ELSE
     ECHO PLAYER A strong blow has shattered one of the panes of glass of the window\
creating a hole large enough for entry.
   ENDIF
   CLEARVERB
ENDIF
;





